The paper focuses on document image representation using visual features, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also evaluates the performance of different types of features in classification, clustering, and retrieval tasks, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of hybrid architectures, which is a topic in natural language processing (cs.CL) that is relevant to document image representation.
